    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If you are using an account that has funds in mainnet and sign a transaction in Hardhat for a forked network (or even local network) with chain id 1, and if that transaction is valid in mainnet (correct nonce, etc.), _and_ if someone has access to that signed transaction, then it can be just propagated and mined in mainnet.\r\n\r\nIt's a somewhat contrived example, but not impossible.",
